  "doc_id": "42172",
  "text": "Locating a string in a larger text has applications with text editing, compiler frontends and web browsers, Internet search engines, computer security, and DNA sequence analysis. Early string searching algorithms such as Aho-Corasick [CITATION_1] , Boyer-Moore [CITATION_2] and Rabin-Karp [CITATION_3] efficiently match a finite set of input strings against an input text.",
